{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: encounter-eu-hdr_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Encounter instance conforming to the EncounterEuHdr
    profile (EU Hospital Discharge Report). Captures an inpatient encounter
    with the hospital, the responsible practitioner, the encounter period,
    clinical reasons, and service type.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: EncounterEuHdr
    Fixed elements:
      status : #completed (using full URI notation — see below)
      class  : $v3-ActCode#IMP (inpatient)

  THREE-COLUMN HTML TABLE
    Column 1 — Location (hospital name, city, country)
    Column 2 — Encounter period (start – end date range, or single date)
    Column 3 — Reason(s) as an HTML `<ul><li>` list

  STATUS — FULL URI NOTATION
    Uniquely among the templates, encounter status uses a full URI rather than
    the short `#code` form:
      * status = http://hl7.org/fhir/encounter-status#completed "completed"
    This is valid FSH but differs from the `* status = #completed` pattern
    used by all other templates. It may be required by the EncounterEuHdr
    profile's binding strength or was an early authoring choice.

  DATE RESOLUTION — DUAL FIELD NAMES WITH ?? COALESCING
    Encounter periods may be supplied under two different field name conventions
    in the source data. The template resolves this with chained ?? operators:
      {% set theStart = encounter.start ?? encounter.episodestart ?? null %}
      {% set theEnd   = encounter.end   ?? encounter.episodeend   ?? null %}
    This allows the caller to supply either `start`/`end` or
    `episodestart`/`episodeend` — whichever is non-null is used.

  SINGLE-DATE VS DATE-RANGE DISPLAY (HTML only)
    When theStart equals theEnd (same-day encounter), the HTML cell shows a
    single date. Otherwise a "start - end" range is shown.

  REASON COLUMN — HTML LIST ACCUMULATION PATTERN
    The encounter reasons are rendered as an HTML `<ul><li>` list in HTML
    column 3. A local variable `rea` is built by string accumulation across
    the reasonCode loop:
      {% set rea = "<ul>" %}
      {% for r in encounter.reason %}
      * reasonCode[+] = {{ r.system }}#{{ r.code }} "{{ r.display }}"
      {% set rea = rea ~ "<li>" ~ r.display ~ "</li>" %}
      {% endfor %}
      {% set rea = rea ~ "</ul>" %}
      {{ addHTML_td(rea) }}
    The HTML markup is passed as a raw string into addHTML_td() — the caller
    must ensure the vi7eti/SYNDERAI stylesheet renders `<ul>/<li>` correctly
    inside a table cell, and that addHTML_td() does not HTML-escape the tags.

  PARTICIPANT AND SERVICE PROVIDER — BOTH CONDITIONAL
    serviceProvider references `hospital.instanceorganization` (conditional).
    participant[0] references `hospital.instancepractitioner` (conditional).
    Both use the same `hospital.*` variables as provider-as-hospital_fsh.twig,
    implying that template must be invoked before this one in the same bundle.
    participant[0].period.end is additionally conditional on `encounter.end`.

  SERVICE TYPE — LOOP
    `encounter.service` is an array; each entry produces one `serviceType[+]`
    CodeableConcept.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌───────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                      │ Type     │ Description                                  │
  ├───────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ encounter.instanceid          │ string   │ Unique resource id.                          │
  │ encounter.start               │ string?  │ ISO 8601 period start (primary field name).  │
  │ encounter.episodestart        │ string?  │ ISO 8601 period start (alternate field name).│
  │ encounter.end                 │ string?  │ ISO 8601 period end (primary field name).    │
  │ encounter.episodeend          │ string?  │ ISO 8601 period end (alternate field name).  │
  │ encounter.reason              │ object[] │ Array of reason objects.                     │
  │   [n].system                  │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                            │
  │   [n].code                    │ string   │   Reason concept code.                       │
  │   [n].display                 │ string   │   Reason display text (also in HTML list).   │
  │ encounter.service             │ object[] │ Array of service type objects.               │
  │   [n].system                  │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                            │
  │   [n].code                    │ string   │   Service type code.                         │
  │   [n].display                 │ string   │   Service type display text.                 │
  │ hospital.instanceorganization │ string?  │ UUID of the hospital Organisation resource.  │
  │                               │          │ When present, emits serviceProvider.         │
  │ hospital.instancepractitioner │ string?  │ UUID of the Practitioner resource. When      │
  │                               │          │ present, emits participant[0].               │
  │ hospital.name                 │ string   │ Hospital display name for HTML td 1.         │
  │ hospital.city                 │ string   │ City for HTML td 1.                          │
  │ hospital.country              │ string   │ Country for HTML td 1.                       │
  │ patient.instanceid            │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                │
  │ patient.name                  │ string   │ Full display name for the subject Reference. │
  └───────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    http://hl7.org/fhir/encounter-status — #completed (full URI notation)
    $v3-ActCode                          — #IMP (inpatient encounter class)
    $v3-ParticipationType                — #PPRF "primary performer"
    Reason and service type codesystem URIs — caller-supplied

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-07, 2026-03-17
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Encounter-" ~ encounter.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: EncounterEuHdr
Title: "Encounter (HDR)"
Description: "Encounter"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ encounter.instanceid }}"

{# HEAD bag: three-column table header #}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Location") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Period") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reason(s)") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── Fixed status and class ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Note: status uses full URI notation (unique among all templates).
  class #IMP = inpatient encounter.
#}
* status = http://hl7.org/fhir/encounter-status#completed "completed"
* class  = $v3-ActCode#IMP

{#
  ── Service provider and participant (both conditional) ──────────────────────
  serviceProvider: hospital Organisation — emitted when instanceorganization is set.
  participant[0]: primary performer (Practitioner) — emitted when instancepractitioner
  is set. participant[0].period.end is additionally conditional on encounter.end.
  Both reference resources generated by provider-as-hospital_fsh.twig.
#}
{% if hospital.instanceorganization is not empty %}
* serviceProvider = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ hospital.instanceorganization }})
{% endif %}
{# HTML td 1: location string assembled from hospital fields #}
{{ addHTML_td(hospital.name  ~ ", " ~ hospital.city ~ ", " ~ hospital.country) }}

{% if hospital.instancepractitioner is not empty %}
* participant[0].type = $v3-ParticipationType#PPRF "primary performer"
{% if encounter.end is not empty %}
* participant[0].period.end = "{{ encounter.end }}"
{% endif %}
* participant[0].individual = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ hospital.instancepractitioner }})
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Period — dual field name resolution with ?? coalescing ───────────────────
  theStart and theEnd each resolve from two possible source field names.
  The caller may supply either encounter.start/end or encounter.episodestart/end.
#}
{% set theStart = encounter.start ?? encounter.episodestart ?? null %}
{% set theEnd   = encounter.end   ?? encounter.episodeend   ?? null %}
{% if theStart is not empty %}
* period.start = "{{ theStart }}"
{% endif %}
{% if theEnd is not empty %}
* period.start = "{{ theEnd }}"
{% endif %}

{#
  ── HTML td 2: period display ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Single date when start == end; "start - end" range otherwise.
#}
{% if theStart is not empty or theEnd is not empty %}
{% if theStart == theEnd %}
{{ addHTML_td( theEnd|date('d-M-Y') ) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td( theStart|date('d-M-Y') ~ " - " ~ theEnd|date('d-M-Y') ) }}
{% endif %}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td( " ? ") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Subject reference ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── Reason codes + HTML list accumulation ────────────────────────────────────
  FSH: one reasonCode[+] rule per reason (system#code "display").
  HTML: a <ul><li> list is built by string accumulation into the `rea` variable,
  then passed to addHTML_td(). The HTML markup is embedded as a raw string —
  ensure the stylesheet and addHTML_td() render it unescaped.
#}
{% set rea = "<ul>" %}
{% for r in encounter.reason %}
* reasonCode[+] = {{ r.system }}#{{ r.code }} "{{ r.display }}"
{% set rea = rea ~ "<li>" ~ r.display ~ "</li>" %}
{% endfor %}
{% set rea = rea ~ "</ul>" %}
{{ addHTML_td(rea) }}

{#
  ── Service type — loop ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  One serviceType[+] CodeableConcept per entry in encounter.service.
#}
{% for s in encounter.service %}
* serviceType[+] = {{ s.system }}#{{ s.code }} "{{ s.display }}"
{% endfor %}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative — body rows only (Pattern 1) ─────────────────────────────
  emitHTML() only — HEAD bag not flushed inside text.div.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
